<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1618] static structMap in FieldMetaData is not thread safe and can lead to deadlocks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1618</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Generated thrift structs use static initializers to add metadata to the static &apos;structMap&apos; field in FieldMetaData. Since the thrift structs may be separate classes, the static initializers can be executed on different threads. The addStructMetaDataMap method does not synchronize access and uses a standard HashMap which is not thread safe. This can lead to corruption of the structMap and in some cases deadlocks due to corrupt entries in the map during a put operation. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The easy fix is to use a thread safe map for the structMap.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another fix is to just retrieve the field directly from the class in the &apos;getStructMetaDataMap&apos; using reflection. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve confirmed the deadlock in 0.2. I looked at the 0.8 code and confirmed the bug is still present. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;jdk 1.6&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
